org.apache.river.test.spec.lookupdiscovery

Class ConstructorNullElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestEnvironment

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Test, TestEnvironment
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AddGroupsNullElement

    public class ConstructorNullElement
extends AbstractBaseTest
    This class verifies that the LookupDiscovery utility class operates in a manner consistent with the specification. In particular, this class verifies that when the parameter input to the constructor contains at least 1 null element, a NullPointerException is thrown. The environment in which this class expects to operate is as follows:

    • no lookup services
    • an instance of the lookup discovery utility constructed using a set of groups in which at least 1 element is null

    If the lookup discovery utility functions as specified, then upon attempting to construct an instance of the lookup discovery utility using a set of groups containing at least one null element, a NullPointerException will occur.
